Subject: Hangzhou Wenlan High School 
To: Francis
Content:
The Wenlan High School is a secondary school located in Hangzhou, Zhejiang Province, China. It is formerly known as High School Afflicted to Hangzhou University, which was established in 1956. The school was renamed Xuejun High school in 1970. In 2003, the school moved to its current Tongyi Road campus. The school campus now consists of 9.87 hectares of land, classrooms and laboratories, a boarding school and sporting facilities, with total investment of approximately 135 million yuan. Wenlan high school was consistently ranked as one of the top schools in Hangzhou, and has produced students who topped in High school entrance examination over the years. 
